Research Apdex (Application Performance Index) scoring in depth: its standardization, industry adoption, and known limitations. Cover the official Apdex Alliance specification (Apdex 1.1), the exact formula, the standard rating scale (Excellent ≥0.94, Good 0.85–0.94, Fair 0.70–0.85, Poor 0.50–0.70, Unacceptable <0.50), and what organizations developed and ratified the standard.

Investigate how the 4T frustration threshold (4 times the satisfied threshold) was chosen. Is there empirical user experience research backing the 4T multiplier, or was it an arbitrary engineering decision? Are there published studies comparing user satisfaction at 1T, 2T, 4T, and 8T thresholds?

Research which APM vendors have adopted Apdex natively: New Relic, Dynatrace, AppDynamics, Datadog. What default thresholds do these vendors use, and do they allow per-endpoint threshold customization? What do these vendors recommend as the T value for different transaction types (web requests, background jobs, database queries)?

Cover the known failure modes and criticisms of Apdex: how does it behave with bimodal latency distributions? What happens when a cache hit/miss split creates two clearly separate latency populations? How does Apdex score masking work when a small number of extremely slow requests are hidden by a large volume of fast requests? Are there proposed alternatives or extensions to Apdex from academic literature or industry practice?

Research weighted Apdex: what use cases justify weighting transactions differently, and how do APM vendors implement weighted scoring? What are the trade-offs between weighted and unweighted Apdex for dashboards and alerting?
